label: Type 1 diabetes diagnosed

label: Age at first received solid food or non-human milk (months)
definition: Approximate age in months when the child first received solid food or non-human milk.

label: Different food groups consumed
definition: Sum of food groups consumed yesterday, based on WHO diet diversity for all children. Values ranged from 0-7. The 7 foods groups used for tabulation of this indicator were: (a) grains, roots and tubers; (b) legumes and nuts; (c) dairy products (milk, yogurt, cheese); (d) flesh foods (meat, fish, poultry and liver/organ meats); (e) eggs; (f) vitamin-A rich fruits and vegetables; (g) other fruits and vegetables. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Built-environment
definition: MIxS environmental package

label: Environment (biome)
definition: Biomes are defined based on factors such as plant structures, leaf types, plant spacing, and other factors like climate. Biome should be treated as the descriptor of the broad ecological context of a sample. Examples include: desert, taiga, deciduous wood

label: Environment (material)
definition: The environmental material level refers to the material that was displaced by the sample, or material in which a sample was embedded, prior to the sampling event. Environmental material terms are generally mass nouns. Examples include: air, soil, or water

label: Local environment
definition: Environmental feature level includes geographic environmental features. Compared to biome, feature is a descriptor of the more local environment. Examples include: harbor, cliff, or lake. EnvO (v 2013-06-14) terms can be found via the link: www.environmentontology.org

label: City, village, or region
definition: The geographical origin of the sample as defined by the country or sea name followed by specific region name. Country or sea names should be chosen from the INSDC country list (http://insdc.org/country.html), or the GAZ ontology (v 1.512)  (http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/GAZ)

label: Depth
definition: depth is defined as the vertical distance below local surface, e.g. for sediment or soil samples depth is measured from sediment or soil surface, respectivly. Depth can be reported as an interval for subsurface samples

label: Elevation (feet)
definition: the elevation of the sampling site as measured by the vertical distance from mean sea level

label: Urban or rural site
definition: Location of the household when the child was born, urban or rural

label: Host common name
definition: common name of the host, e.g. human

label: Host organism
definition: scientific name of the host, e.g. homo sapiens

label: Human or Animal
definition: MIxS environmental package

label: Family move
definition: boolean; did the household move

label: Age (days)
definition: the animal's or human's age counted in days

label: Age (years)
definition: age of host at the time of sampling; relevant scale depends on species and study, e.g. could be seconds for amoebae or centuries for trees. The unit of age is year.

label: Age 1st solid food given (days)
variable: Day of introduction of solid food

label: Animal cage num in experiment
definition: Cage # designated for that experiment

label: Baby's delivery mode
definition: Method of delivery (newborn)

label: Bee colony tetracycline
definition: was the bee colony treated with tetracycline

label: Bee larval tetracycline
definition: were bee larvae treated with tetracycline?

label: CCECAI
definition: Canine Chronic Enteropathy Clinical Activity Index

label: CFTR mutation (F508del)
definition: Whether the patient was homozygous or heterozygous for mutations at the cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) gene, or whether they had other mutations relevant to cystic fibrosis.

label: Canine breed
definition: Canine Breed

label: Child's diet
variable: diet_3 | diet_2 | Formula or breast milk
definition: overall, what the main source of nutrition for the child?

label: Child's diet (by month)
definition: For each month, what was the main source of nutrition for the child?

label: Child's diet first three days
definition: Milk feeding during the first three days of life: mother's breast milk, formula or something else (e.g. combination of beast milk and formula, or not reported)

label: Forced expiratory volume (%)
definition: The amount of air you can force from your lungs in one second, expressed as a percentage of maximum.

label: Forced expiratory volume (L)
definition: The amount of air you can force from your lungs in one second, expressed in liters.

label: Host body habitat
definition: original body habitat where the sample was obtained from

label: Host body product
definition: substance produced by the body, e.g. stool, mucus, where the sample was obtained from. For Foundational Model of Anatomy Ontology (FMA) (v 3.1) terms, please see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/FMA

label: Host body site
definition: name of body site where the sample was obtained from

label: Host diet
definition: type of diet depending on the host, for animals omnivore, herbivore etc., for humans high-fat, meditteranean etc.; can include multiple diet types

label: Host family relationship
definition: relationships to other hosts in the same study; can include multiple relationships

label: Host life stage
definition: description of life stage of host

label: Host total mass
definition: total mass of the host at collection, the unit depends on host

label: Hydrocephalus
definition: Hydrocephalus is an active distension of the ventricular system of the brain resulting from inadequate passage of CSF from its point of production within the cerebral ventricles to its point of absorption into the systemic circulation.

label: Mother or child
definition: Choose samples obtained from the mother, from the child, or both.

label: Presence of pets or farm animals
definition: specification of presence of pets or farm animals in the environment of subject, if yes the animals should be specified; can include multiple animals present

label: Sex
definition: physical sex of the host

label: Study group
definition: Describes treatment, infection status, etc.

label: Treatment
definition: A processual entity whose completion is hypothesized (by a healthcare provider) to alleviate the signs and symptoms associated with a disorder

label: Weight loss in last three months
definition: specification of weight loss in the last three months, if yes should be further specified to include amount of weight loss

label: psn
definition: participant identifier

label: Maternal age at birth
definition: Maternal age at birth

label: Mom reported antibiotic use during pregnancy
definition: Mom reported antibiotic use during pregnancy

label: Mom reported gestational diabetes
definition: Mom reported gestational diabetes

label: Pathogens per month
definition: mean number of enteropathogens detected per surveillance stool in the observation window

label: Pathogens per month excluding Campylobacter
definition: mean number of enteropathogens detected per surveillance stool in the observation window, excluding Campylobacter

label: Percentage of diarrheal samples for Campylobacter-pos
variable: percentage of diarrheal samples positive for campylobacter
definition: percentage of diarrheal samples in the observation window that were tested positive for Campylobacter

label: Percentage of surveillance samples for pathogens-pos excluding Campylobacter
variable: percentage of surveillance samples positive for pathogens excluding campylobacter
definition: percentage of surveillance samples in the observation window that were tested positive for pathogens, excluding Campylobacter

label: Percentage of surveillance stools for Campylobacter-pos
variable: percentage of surveillance stools positive for campylobacter
definition: percentage of surveillance stools in the observation window that were tested positive for Campylobacter

label: DNA extraction date
definition: Describes when the DNA was extracted

label: SRA Accession ID
definition: An accession number assigned to DNA sequencing data by Sequence Read Archive (SRA).

label: Age at sample collection (months)
variable: age_at_collection_months | age in months | Age of donor at time of fecal sample collection (months) | Age (months)

label: Sample collection date
definition: The time of sampling, either as an instance (single point in time) or interval. In case no exact time is available, the date/time can be right truncated i.e. all of these are valid times: 2008-01-23T19:23:10+00:00; 2008-01-23T19:23:10; 2008-01-23; 2008-01

label: Sample collection device or method
definition: The method or device employed for collecting the sample

label: Sample collection time post infection (days)
definition: Describes when the samples were collected following infection

label: Skin type swabbed
definition: Describes the type of skin swabbed (lesion, non-lesion (contralateral skin), etc)
codebookValues: Lesion, Border (adjacent to lesion), Normal (Contralateral skin)

label: Subject ID
variable: Infant | subject | subject_id | host_subject_id | Child ID | SubjectID

label: Sequencing batch
definition: In which batch were samples sequenced together

label: Sequencing center
definition: At which center were samples sequenced

label: Affected by atopic dermatitis (yes/no)
definition: Affected or Unaffected

label: Corneometry
definition: Epidermal Moisture content

label: Degree of hairloss
definition: Degree of hairloss

label: Degree of inflammation (mm squared)
definition: Describes the degree (area) of inflammation after a patient was exposed to leishmania antigen

label: Degree of skin readness
definition: Degree of skin readness

label: Degree of skin thickening
definition: Degree of skin thickening

label: Ear thickness (mm)
definition: Measurement of ear thickness of a mouse

label: Lesion size (mm squared)
definition: Describes the size of the lesion at the time the swab was collected

label: Pathology score
definition: Pathology score used during leishmania infections
codebookValues: 0- no lesion, 1- redness/swelling, 2- pinna deformation, 3- ulceration, 4- partial tissue loss, 5- total tissue loss

label: Skin lesion duration (days)
definition: Describes how long a lesion was present before swabbing it

label: Transepidermal water loss (g/m2 h)
definition: Transepidermal water loss

label: Axillary lesion score after treatment
definition: LesionScore_Axilla_Visit3

label: Axillary lesion score before treatment
definition: LesionScore_Axilla_visit1

label: Axillary lesion score during treatment
definition: LesionScore_Axilla_Visit2

label: Drug usage
definition: any drug used by subject and the frequency of usage; can include multiple drugs used

label: Groin lesion score after treatment
definition: LesionScore_Groin_Visit3

label: Groin lesion score before treatment
definition: LesionScore_Groin_visit1

label: Groin lesion score during treatment
definition: LesionScore_Groin_Visit2

label: Number of treatments
definition: Describes the number of treatments needed before the lesion healed

label: Pinna lesion score after treatment
definition: LesionScore_Pinna_Visit3

label: Pinna lesion score before treatment
definition: LesionScore_Pinna_Visit1

definition: LesionScore_Pinna_Visit2
